28/12/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Justice Minister Vesna Skare-Ozbolt vowed to strengthen the judicial reform process next year, during a meeting with Croatian court chiefs in Zagreb Tuesday (27 December). The talks focused on the results of sector restructuring as well as the latest amendments to laws regulating the organisation of the judiciary.
On Wednesday, employees in Croatia's state services sector are staging a daylong strike demanding higher salaries and better working conditions. The protestors include customs officers, policemen and local administration employees. (Novi list, HINA - 28/12/05; HRT, HINA - 27/12/05) 
